ria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104thz1665702609551.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/thz1665702609551.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/thz1665702609551.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"thz1665702609551\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Label Font\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Font to use for the label, and for tool tip text for widgets (if they support tool tips). The listed fonts are determines by the application's <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thz1665702609551__section_c5r_zck_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1225216e54\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thz1665702609551__p_d109880e1_d109881e1_d109882e1\">This property can be set only via the pop-up menu on a\n        label. You can set the default font in the application's <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thz1665702609551__p_d109883e1_d109884e1_d109885e1\">By default, the label rectangle includes a 2 pixel\n        margin around the text, which can cause the label to wrap, even if there appears to be\n        enough space for the text. To prevent this from happening:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"thz1665702609551__ol_rdv_ddk_cxb\">\n<li class=\"li\">Set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Label Font</span>to <code class=\"ph codeph\">FormText</code>This makes the label\n          rectangle behave as if it has no margin, preventing unnecessary wrapping.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Ensure that the FormText font defined in <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>is the same as\n          font0.<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"thz1665702609551__pre_x5k_hdk_cxb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;usys.ini\n[screen]\nfont0=Arial,Western,8,regular\nFormText=Arial,Western,8,regular</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thz1665702609551__section_xnw_3dk_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1225216e89\">Applies To</h2>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ngv1688454370143.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ngv1688454370143.html\" title=\"A label displays text on a component, such as the name of an associated field or an instruction to the user.\">Label</a></p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifp1665702614021.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Labels in Forms and Reports</a><p>Labels are objects that contain static. Most labels are associated with a field, but unassociated labels can be used for any static text on the component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616089\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616089\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Label Font Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Label Font Font to use for the label, and for tool tip text for widgets (if they support tool tips). The listed fonts are determines by the application's .ini file. Description This property can be set only via the pop-up menu on a label. You can set the default font in the application's .ini file. By default, the label rectangle includes a 2 pixel margin around the text, which can cause the label to wrap, even if there appears to be enough space for the text. To prevent this from happening: Set Label Font to FormText This makes the label rectangle behave as if it has no margin, preventing unnecessary wrapping. Ensure that the FormText font defined in usys.ini is the same as font0. ;usys.ini [screen] font0=Arial,Western,8,regular FormText=Arial,Western,8,regular Copy Applies To Label Related Links Labels in Forms and Reports Labels are objects that contain static. Most labels are associated with a field, but unassociated labels can be used for any static text on the component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}